Score(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:\n        total_sum = sum(nums)\n        left_sum = 0\n        max_score = float('-inf')\n        \n        for num in nums:\n            left_sum += num\n            max_score = max(max_score, left_sum, total_sum - left_sum + num)\n        \n        return max_score\n```\n\nThis solution calculates the total sum of the array once and then iterates through the array, maintaining a running sum (`left_sum`). For each index, it calculates the sum of the elements from the start to the current index and the sum of the elements from the current index to the end, updating the `max_score` accordingly. This approach ensures that the solution is efficient, with a time complexity of O(n).", "estimated_date": 1648339200000}